# Use data-testid for Testable Components

Always add `data-testid` attributes to interactive components and key UI elements that need to be tested.

## Why

- `data-testid` provides stable, reliable selectors for tests
- Avoids flaky tests that rely on accessible names, text content, or DOM structure
- Makes tests more resilient to UI changes that don't affect functionality

## Rules

- Add `data-testid` to all interactive components (buttons, links, inputs, dropdowns, etc.)
- Use descriptive, kebab-case names (e.g., `data-testid="mode-toggle-trigger"`)
- Prefer `data-testid` over role-based queries when the component is complex or has multiple similar elements
- Use `getByTestId` or `queryByTestId` in tests instead of fragile selectors

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - relying on accessible name matching
const triggers = screen.getAllByRole("button", { name: /toggle theme/i });
expect(triggers[0]).toBeInTheDocument();

// ✅ GOOD - using data-testid
<DropdownMenuTrigger data-testid="mode-toggle-trigger">
  ...
</DropdownMenuTrigger>

const trigger = screen.getByTestId("mode-toggle-trigger");
expect(trigger).toBeInTheDocument();
```
